Comment: The QP opening and the Classical reply.
The QP opening and the Classical reply.
An unusual variant, designed to open the game.
Developing and attacking the advanced Pawn.
Countering with a developing move that defends the Pawn.
Unable to maintain the Pawn, Stock exchanges.
The recapture puts Diemer's KN on its natural square.
Presumably, to prevent a move of P-Q5 by Diemer.
Down a pawn, Diemer plays aggressively. He has 3 pieces developed to just 1 for Stock.
With QB3 occupied by a Pawn, Stock must play his QN to Q2 instead. His position is beginning to get cramped.
Diemer pressures the natural weakness, the KB2 square.
Blocking the diagonal of the Bishop.
Stock resigns. If 9...KxN, 10 BxP ch would force his King into the open. 10 O-O ch or 10 Q-R5 ch or 10 Q-B3 ch would also be good options for Diemer.
